<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>VT 365 Diesel Engine - 2004 Model Year - ELECTRONICALLY CONTROLLED VARIABLE GEOMETRY TURBOCHARGER (VGT) -
        Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="s26502.4">
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcproc id="s26502.4.1" graphiccount="11">
            <title>Variable Geometry Turbocharger (VGT) and Components</title>
            <figure id="f2650221" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd15/D1553.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>VGT bracket</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place VGT bracket in engine valley by putting right side of bracket under EGR cooler
                    coolant inlet tube. Then lower left side over bolt holes.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650222" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd15/D1550.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>VGT bracket bolts</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install four M8 x 20 mounting bolts to secure VGT bracket to crankcase. Tighten bolts to
                    the standard torque .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650224" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd15/D1555.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Lubrication for O-rings on oil drain tube for VGT</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two new oil drain tube O-rings and lubricate both O-rings with clean engine
                    oil.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove cap and install drain tube in the high-pressure oil pump cover.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If not immediately installing the VGT, install a cover over the oil drain tube.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f2650225" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd15/D1514A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>VGT alignment dowels and bosses</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Alignment dowel</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Alignment boss</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use alignment dowels to position VGT on bosses of forward and middle mounting
                    brackets.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the oil drain tube cap (if it was installed) and lower VGT on mounting brackets
                    and on oil drain tube.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Coat bolt threads for three M8 x 30 flange head bolts with anti-seize compound and
                    secure VGT to mounting bracket.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten bolts to the special torque .</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650227" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD15/D15103.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Exhaust adapter V-clamp for VGT</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the exhaust outlet cover, install exhaust piping, and tighten VGT exhaust adapter
                    V-clamp to the special torque .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove cover on oil supply port on the oil cooler cover assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install and lubricate a new O-ring on oil supply tube.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650208" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD15/D15102.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Oil supply tube for VGT to oil cooler cover assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Oil supply tube</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Mounting bolt</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install VGT oil supply tube in oil supply line port in the oil cooler cover assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install and tighten the M8 x 20 flange head bolt. Torque the oil supply tube bolt to the
                    standard torque .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650229" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD15/D1535.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Prelubrication of VGT bearings</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, prelubricate VGT bearings when installing the VGT.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Prelubricate the oil inlet hole of the VGT with clean engine oil and spin compressor
                    wheel several times to coat bearings with oil. Refill the oil inlet hole up to oil supply tube
                    mounting surface.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650230" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD15/D15101.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Oil supply tube for VGT</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Oil supply tube</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Mounting bolt (2)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position oil supply tube over a new gasket and secure with two M8 x 20 bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten to the standard torque . Alternate tightening between both bolts until the
                    correct torque is reached.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650231" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd15/D1545A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Breather tube with pitot tube in crankcase breather</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove cap and press pitot tube in the crankcase breather until it locks in place.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650232" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD15/D15104.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Air inlet duct to VGT</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">VGT</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Air inlet duct</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove cap and align the arrow on the inlet duct with the mark on the inlet housing
                    opening on VGT and press on the VGT.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure air inlet duct to VGT by tightening hose clamp to the special torque .</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650205" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD13/D13143.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Air inlet duct</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Lube oil fill extension tube</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Breather hose</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Air inlet duct</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove cap from the valve cover and thread the oil fill extension tube in the valve
                    cover and torque to the special torque .
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
